no injury, Dcosteftor, and heroes, but I have been troubled by your past life, to whom it is more fitting that you should have faith. But my dear friend will repay those who are angry with me. for I did not want to be poor, I did not want to apply my mind to anyone else, but please,
because I bore the ignorance of the prison with a sorrowful mind; Again I did not fear that I would kill you, for I had no use for you: indeed I lost myself. I did not put my mind to these things in you, nor to any other person, for you can make me think of many people. I had known the true elders, at a time when danger threatened them from the perfidious king: and I had indeed perfected the most benevolence towards them. hzc cft cft trozeniiorum cai readitas cai opto; as God's favorite, because ipfiuser uos beneuolen tiam and the benefice conferred on me fint all the beneuoles, then ipie feruatus
